      "writtenOn": "2017-01-03T20:29:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems weird to me. Not because we\u0027re modifying this field that should be constant*, but because we return a different color space without doing any conversion. If I look at the only other two implementations of this virtual, I see\n\n SkImage_Generator::getROPixels: If I follow this correctly, we\u0027ll ask the generator to use dstColorSpace. For an SkCodecImageGenerator, this will do some sort of conversion, right?\n\n SkImage_Gpu::getROPixels: This one appears to ignore dstColorSpace.\n\n* Maybe that is problematic too? My initial thought was that we\u0027re modifying everything about the dst SkBitmap anyway - we could have instead set a modified info and then set the pixel ref - this is just simpler and clearer about our intent. But then we get into a situation (just like we do here) where the color space on the SkBitmap does not match the one on the SkPixelRef. I know the SkImageInfos can mismatch for width and height (i.e. if the SkBitmap represents a subset). Are we sure that clients will trust the right SkColorSpace (presumably the SkBitmap, in this case) if they do not match?",
